



Sir
Maryland the 8th of April 1770



Yours Acquanting me that Mr West had Promissed to be at your house this Afternoon, In order to Run the Dividing Line between Washington & Spencer, came to hand,1 Tho am afrade Shall not be able to give my self the Pleasure of Wating on You in the Morning, Owing to a Verry seveare Could, which affects me in Such a Manner, that I can scarsly git a Moments Rest. Should I be Better in the Morning will wate on you Arly. However should I not, dont Doubt but you and Mr West will Lay the Dividing Line of, agreable to the True Intent and Desine thereof. I am yr Most Hble servt

Tho. Han. Marshall

